ccre.cluck

Class CluckNode

  • java.lang.Object
    • ccre.cluck.CluckNode

  • public class CluckNode
extends java.lang.Object
    A message router for Cluck. Allows for listeners to subscribe to various channels, and allows sending data to whichever listeners want the data.

    • Field Summary

      Fields

      java.lang.String nodeID
      A hopefully-unique identifier for this node, and this node only.
      protected CCollection<CluckSubscriptionListener> subscriptionListeners
      The listeners that want to know when a new channel is subscribed to, or when a channel loses all subscribers.
      protected CCollection<CluckChannelListener> wildcarded
      The listeners that want to receive all data coming across this node.

    • Constructor Detail

      • CluckNode

        public CluckNode()
        Create a new CluckNode and generate its nodeID. Parts of a node ID:
        • The hashCode of the CluckNode
        • The current time in milliseconds
        • The microedition.platform system property.
        • The type of Networking subsystem in use.
        See Also:
        Object.hashCode(), System.currentTimeMillis(), System.getProperty(java.lang.String), Network.getPlatformType()

    • Method Detail

      • subscribeToSubscriptions

        public void subscribeToSubscriptions(CluckSubscriptionListener listener)
        Register a subscripting listener. Whenever a channel receives its first subscription or a channel loses all subscriptions, the listener will be notified. The listener will also be notified right now of all current channels with subscriptions.
        Parameters:
        listener - the listener to register.
        See Also:
        unsubscribeFromSubscriptions(ccre.cluck.CluckSubscriptionListener)

      • unsubscribeFromSubscriptions

        public void unsubscribeFromSubscriptions(CluckSubscriptionListener listener)
        Removes a listener previously subscribed using subscribeToSubscriptions.
        Parameters:
        listener - the listener to remove.
        See Also:
        subscribeToSubscriptions(ccre.cluck.CluckSubscriptionListener)

      • subscribe

        public void subscribe(java.lang.String channel,
             CluckChannelListener listener)
        Subscribes to the specified channel, or all channels if the specified channel is null. The specified listener will be notified whenever new data is received over the specified channel.
        Parameters:
        channel - the channel to listen on, or null to listen on all channels.
        listener - the listener to notify when data is received.
        See Also:
        unsubscribe(java.lang.String, ccre.cluck.CluckChannelListener)

      • unsubscribe

        public void unsubscribe(java.lang.String channel,
               CluckChannelListener listener)
        Removes a listener previously added using subscribe.
        Parameters:
        channel - the channel to remove from, or null to remove from the channel that receives everything.
        listener - the listener to remove.
        See Also:
        subscribe(java.lang.String, ccre.cluck.CluckChannelListener)

      • publish

        public void publish(java.lang.String channel,
           byte[] data)
        Send the given packet of data over the specified channel. All listeners registered on the specified channel or registered on the channel that receives everything will receive the given message.
        Parameters:
        channel - the channel to send over.
        data - the data array to send.

      • publish

        public void publish(java.lang.String channel,
           byte[] data,
           CluckChannelListener ignore)
        Sends data to all listeners except for the specified listener. Works like publish(String, byte[]) otherwise.
        Parameters:
        channel - the channel to send over.
        data - the data array to send.
        ignore - the listener to not notify.
        See Also:
        publish(java.lang.String, byte[])
